msgid ""
"Remove the deprecated ``litestar.contrib.repository`` module. Code still "
"using imports from this module should switch to using ``litestar."
"repository``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:274
msgid ""
"Remove the deprecated ``litestar.contrib.pydantic`` module. Code still using "
"imports from this module should switch to using ``litestar.plugins."
"pydantic``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:283
msgid ""
"Remove the deprecated module ``litestar.contrib.minijnja``. This module was "
"created with a typo in its name (`minijnja` instead of `minijinja`). Instead "
"``litestar.contrib.minijinja`` should be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:291
msgid ""
"New ``round_trip: bool`` parameter to :class:`~litestar.contrib.pydantic."
"PydanticPlugin` allows serializing types like ``pydanctic.Json`` correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:301
msgid ""
"Remove the deprecated ``litestar.contrib.minijinja.minijinja_from_state`` "
"function. Instead use a callable that receives the minijinja ``State`` "
"object as first argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:310
msgid ""
"Use ``litestar[piccolo]`` extra installation target and ``litestar_piccolo`` "
"plugin instead: https://github.com/litestar-org/litestar-piccolo"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:326
msgid ""
"Middlewares inheriting from :class:`~litestar.middleware.base."
"ASGIMiddleware` will now have zero runtime cost when they are excluded e.g. "
"via the ``scope`` or ``exclude_opt_key`` options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:330
msgid ""
"Previously, the base middleware was always being invoked for every request, "
"evaluating the exclusion criteria, and then calling the user defined "
"middleware functions. If a middleware had defined ``scopes = (ScopeType."
"HTTP,)``, it would still be called for *every* request, regardless of the "
"scope type. Only for requests with the type ``HTTP``, it would then call the "
"user's function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:337
msgid "This behaviour is still true for the legacy ``AbstractMiddleware``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:339
msgid ""
"With *zero cost exclusion*, the exclusion is being evaluated statically. At "
"app creation time, when route handlers are registered and their middleware "
"stacks are being built, a middleware that is to be excluded will simply not "
"be included in the stack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:345
msgid ""
"Even though this change is marked as breaking, no runtime behaviour "
"difference is expected. Some test cases may break though if they relied on "
"the fact that the middleware wrapper created by ``ASGIMiddleware`` was "
"always being called"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:355
msgid "Support unwrapping ``ReadOnly`` type in schemas like:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:357
msgid ""
"from typing import ReadOnly, TypedDict\n"
"\n"
"class User(TypedDict):\n"
"    id: ReadOnly[int]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:364
msgid ""
"``typing_extensions.ReadOnly`` should be used for python versions <3.13."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:371
msgid ""
"Add a new attribute :attr:`~litestar.middleware.ASGIMiddleware."
"should_bypass_for_scope`; A callable which takes in a :class:`~litestar."
"types.Scope` and returns a boolean to indicate whether to bypass the "
"middleware for the current request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:82
msgid ""
"Fix the ``raise_server_exceptions``. This flag has been non-functional (i.e. "
"did not change the behaviour at all) since version 1. This is now fixed, and "
"unhandled exceptions will be re-raised by the test client"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:90
msgid ""
"Fix a bug that could lead to unhandled exceptions raised within websocket "
"handlers, and not derived from :exc:`LitestarException` or :exc:"
"`HTTPException` to be silently swallowed. This would lead to a closing of "
"the WebSocket connection without any indication of an exception"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:319
msgid ""
"Now, in the OpenAPI schema, ``pydantic`` fields with ``default_factory`` are "
"displayed as non-null and not required. Previously, this fields was nullable "
"and not required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes/changelog.rst:379
msgid ""
"Fix a bug in :class:`MsgspecDTO` where a KeyError was raised if a :class:"
"`msgspec.Struct` contained a :class:`~typing.ClassVar`. ClassVars are now "
"correctly skipped when generating field definitions."
msgstr ""
